{"name":"\"Lord Jargle\"","size":"medium","type":"humanoid","tag":"dark elf","alignment":"chaotic good","hitDice":"20","armorName":"none","shieldBonus":0,"natArmorBonus":7,"otherArmorDesc":"10","speed":"30","burrowSpeed":"0","climbSpeed":"0","flySpeed":"0","hover":false,"swimSpeed":"0","customHP":true,"customSpeed":false,"hpText":"160 (20d6)","speedDesc":"30 ft.","strPoints":"14","dexPoints":"16","conPoints":"14","intPoints":"18","wisPoints":"20","chaPoints":"26","blindsight":"0","blind":false,"darkvision":"0","tremorsense":"0","truesight":"120","telepathy":0,"cr":"25","customCr":"1 (200 XP)","customProf":2,"isLegendary":true,"legendariesDescription":"[MON] can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. [MON] regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.","isLair":false,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside its lair, the monster can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the monster can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"The monster can't repeat an effect until they have all been used, and it can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isMythic":false,"mythicDescription":"If the monster's mythic trait is active, it can use the options below as legendary actions for 1 hour after using {Some Ability}.","isRegional":false,"regionalDescription":"The region containing the monster's lair is warped by the creature's presence, which creates one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If the monster dies, the first two effects fade over the course of 3d10 days.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Cosmic Sight","desc":"Lord Jargle has lost his soul, and has gained the ability of partial omnipotence. At will, Lord Jargle can utilize a modified Scrying spell, where he can think of a creature, location, or object in the universe and attempt to see their location. \nWhen using this ability, he makes a Wisdom saving throw with a default DC of 10. It is modified by the following.\n**Knowledge:**\n- _Secondhand_ (Has heard of the target / Knows location position): **+5**\n- _Firsthand_ (Has met target / Has been to location): **+0**\n- _Familiar_ (Is familiar with the target): **-5**\n**Connection:**\n- _Likeness or picture_: **-2**\n- _Possession, garment, or related object_: **-4**\n- _Body part, lock of hair, bit of nail, or the like_: **-10**\n\nOn a failed save, Lord Jargle isn't able to see the target for 24 hours. However, on a successful save, Lord Jargle is able to survey the target however much he wants within a 24 hour period."},{"name":"Fey Ancestry","desc":"[MON] has advantage on saving throws against being charmed, and magic can't put [MON] to sleep."},{"name":"Trance","desc":"Elves don't need to sleep. Instead, they meditate deeply, remaining semiconscious, for 4 hours a day."},{"name":"War Caster","desc":"[MON] has advantage on Constitution saving throws to maintain concentration on spells when he takes damage. When a hostile creature's movement provokes opportunity attacks, [MON]can use their reaction to cast a spell at the creature."},{"name":"Ranged Expert","desc":"Being within 5 feet of a hostile creature doesn't impose disadvantage on [MON]'s ranged attack rolls."},{"name":"Observant","desc":"If [MON] can see a creature's mouth while it is speaking a language [MON] understands, he can interpret what it is saying by reading its lips. [MON] has expertise in perception and investigation."},{"name":"Alert","desc":"[MON] can't be surprised while he is conscious. Other creatures don't gain advantage on attack rolls against [MON] as a result of being unseen by him."},{"name":"Spelldriver","desc":"[MON] is able to cast two spells in one turn. However the second spell must be of 3rd level or lower, and the spells must follow existing action rules."},{"name":"Metamagic","desc":"[MON] can use only one Metamagic option on a spell when he casts it, unless otherwise noted.\n_**Careful Spell**_ When [MON] casts a spell that forces other creatures to make a saving throw, he can protect some of those creatures from the spell's full force. To do so, he spends 1 sorcery point and chooses up to 5 of those creatures. A chosen creature automatically succeeds on its saving throw against the spell.\n_**Subtle Spell**_ When [MON] casts a spell, he can spend 1 sorcery point to cast it without any somatic or verbal components.\n_**Transmuted Spell**_ When [MON] casts a spell that deals a type of damage from the following list, he can spend 1 sorcery point to change that damage type to another listed type: acid, cold, fire, lightning, poison, thunder.\n_**Seeking Spell**_ If [MON] makes an attack roll for a spell and misses, he can spend 2 sorcery points to reroll the d20, and he must use the new roll. [MON] can use Seeking Spell even if he has already used a different Metamagic option during the casting of the spell."},{"name":"Sorcerous Restoration","desc":"[MON] regains 4 expended sorcery points whenever he finishes a short rest."},{"name":"Wild Magic Surge","desc":"When casting a sorcerer spell of 1st level or higher, a d20 is rolled. If a 1 is rolled, roll on the Wild Magic Surge table to create a magical effect. Due to Controlled Chaos, the effect is rolled 3 times and then is chosen from."},{"name":"Tides of Chaos (1 / Long Rest)","desc":"[MON] can gain advantage on one attack roll, ability check, or saving throw. Any time before he regains the use of this feature, he can roll on the Wild Magic Surge table after casting a spell. He then regains the use of this feature."},{"name":"Spell Bombardment","desc":"When [MON] rolls damage for a spell and rolls the highest number possible on any of the dice, choose one of those dice, roll it again and add that to the damage. He can use the feature only once per turn."},{"name":"Spellcasting","desc":"[MON] is a 25th-level spellcaster. Its spellcasting ability is Charisma (spell save DC [CHA SAVE], [CHA ATK] to hit with spell attacks). [MON] has the following spells prepared:\n\n> Cantrips (at will): _Dancing Lights, Fire Bolt, Mage Hand, Message, Prestidigitation, Ray of Frost, Shape Water, Shocking Grasp_\n> 1st level (4 slots): _Burning Hands, Chaos Bolt, False Life, Faerie Fire, Mage Armor_\n> 2nd level (3 slots): _Darkness, Hold Person, Invisibility_\n> 3rd level (3 slots): _Fireball, Major Image_\n> 4th level (3 slots): _Dimension Door, Polymorph_\n> 5th level (3 slots): _Dominate Person, Telekinesis_\n> 6th level (2 slots): _Chain Lightning_\n> 7th level (2 slots): _Reverse Gravity_\n> 8th level (1 slot): _Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting_\n> 9th level (1 slot): _Time Stop_"}],"actions":[{"name":"Multiattack","desc":"[MON] makes two attacks. He can spend both on spells, but the rules of Spelldriver stand."},{"name":"Hands of Chaos","desc":"[MON] sends out 3 spectral hands of pure magical energy. Each hand makes one ranged spell attack against the target. Each hand's damage type is chosen between the following: acid, cold, fire, lightning, poison, and thunder.\n_Ranged Spell Attack:_ [CHA ATK] to hit, range 30/120 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [CHA 1D12] damage."}],"bonusActions":[{"name":"Font of Magic","desc":"[MON] has 30 Sorcery Points. He can transform unexpended sorcery points into one spell slot (1 + spell slot level) on his turn or he can expend one spell slot and gain a number of sorcery points equal to the slot's level."}],"reactions":[{"name":"Bend Luck","desc":"When another creature [MON] can see makes an attack roll, ability check, or saving throw, he can spend 2 sorcery points to roll 1d8 and apply the number rolled as a bonus or penalty to the creature's roll. He can do so after the creature rolls,, but before any effects of the roll occur."}],"legendaries":[{"name":"Cast a spell","desc":"[MON] can cast a spell. He also expends 2 sorcery points."},{"name":"Hands of Chaos","desc":"[MON] can use the Hands of Chaos action."},{"name":"Covered in Chaos (costs 3 actions)","desc":"The targets is completely engulfed in hands of chaos. The target makes an athletics check vs [MON]'s spell attack bonus. On a fail, the target is grappled until the end of the target's next turn and takes [CHA 4d12] damage. The damage type is chosen from the following: acid, cold, fire, lightning, poison, and thunder."}],"mythics":[],"lairs":[],"regionals":[],"sthrows":[{"name":"con","order":2},{"name":"cha","order":5}],"skills":[{"name":"arcana","stat":"int","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"insight","stat":"wis"},{"name":"investigation","stat":"int","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"perception","stat":"wis","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"persuasion","stat":"cha"},{"name":"religion","stat":"int","note":" (ex)"}],"damagetypes":[],"specialdamage":[],"conditions":[{"name":"blinded"}],"languages":[{"name":"Abyssal","speaks":true},{"name":"Celestial","speaks":true},{"name":"Common","speaks":true},{"name":"Elvish","speaks":true},{"name":"Infernal","speaks":true}],"understandsBut":"","shortName":"Lord Jargle","pluralName":"","doubleColumns":true,"separationPoint":9,"damage":[]}